<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_524">Mrs van Gogh</rs> was to turn 56 on 10 September.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="2" xml:id="note-t-2">
                            

<p><rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_737">Alfred Sensier</rs>, <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_40"><hi rend="italics">Etude sur George Michel</hi></ref>. Paris 1873. This monograph consists of a detailed biography, a <hi rend="italics">catalogue raisonné</hi> and etchings after his paintings. The number of etchings per copy vary in number from seventeen to twenty. <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_1228">Michel</rs> is described in the biography as an artist of humble birth, who refused to conform to conventional academic art. Sensier emphasizes Michel’s individualism and his aversion to big cities. Cf. in this context Parsons and McWilliam 1984, pp. 39, 49, 53.</p>
                        </note>
                        
                    
                        <note n="3" xml:id="note-t-3">
                            

    
<p>Regarding this passage from <rs type="person" ref="bio.xml#_590">George Eliot</rs>’s <ref target="biblio.xml#lit_20"><hi rend="italics">Adam Bede</hi></ref>, <ref target="let030.xml#n-1">see letter 30, n. 1</ref><ref target="let030.xml#n-2"> and 2.</ref></p>
                        </note>
                        
                            

                        
                    
